# Docs Site Rules

The docs site is an Astro + Starlight project. Generated content pages are produced from repo assets; do not edit them by hand.

## Generated Content

- `wagents docs generate` — Generates MDX content pages from skills, agents, and MCP servers.
- `wagents docs generate --include-installed` — Opts in to including installed skills from the normalized harness inventory.
- `wagents docs generate --include-drafts` — Includes skills with TODO descriptions.
- **Never hand-edit generated MDX files.** They are overwritten on the next generation run.

## Workflow Commands

```bash
wagents docs init       # One-time: pnpm install in docs/
wagents docs dev        # Generate + launch dev server
wagents docs build      # Generate + static build
wagents docs preview    # Generate + build + preview server
wagents docs clean      # Remove generated content pages
```

## README

- `README.md` is fully generated from repo contents via `wagents readme`.
- `wagents readme --check` exits 1 if `README.md` is stale (use in CI).
- Do not hand-edit `README.md`; modify the source assets and regenerate.

## CI/CD

- The `release-skills.yml` workflow validates assets on every PR.
- It automatically packages and releases skills when a version tag (`v*.*.*`) is pushed.
- Ensure `wagents validate` and `wagents readme --check` pass before merging.

## Docs Steward

- After changes to public APIs, file structure, agent definitions, or skill definitions, invoke the `docs-steward` skill if available to keep documentation in sync.
